node.text:
Beautiful, beaded earrings by @boujee.indigenous 💜 

Here's some #jewelrymaking tips she shared on her beading process! 
▪ Double the thread on your beading needle.
▪ Use an embroidery needle to tack down every two beads to help tell the two apart.
▪ Have a pincushion so your threads don’t get tangled.
▪ Gel superglue is way less messy and doesn’t bleed.
▪ Look in the button aisle for some good centerpieces.
▪ Always leave EXTRA space when you cut out your work! 🌸 #makeitwithmichaels
